import BernoulliRegular.FLT37.LehmerVandiver.PlusCoprime.Sinnott.CyclotomicUnitFamily

/-!
# T-Q1-CSINNOTT: Sinnott `C_S(K‚Āļ)` vs Washington `C_cl(K‚Āļ)` for prime conductor

Per the 2026-05-07 reviewer followup (patch 1, Q1 specialisation
prerequisite), the rank-one Pollaczek specialisation of T-Q1-RANK-ONE
must be stated in terms of the **same** circular-unit subgroup that
Thaine's annihilator theorem (Kuńćera 4.3) consumes ‚ÄĒ which is Sinnott's
`C_S`, not Washington's `C_cl`. Kuńćera explicitly warns that Washington
¬ß15.2 uses the weaker `C_cl`, with the proof requiring modification for
the stronger `C_S` form.

For **prime conductor `p`**, however, Sinnott's `C_S(K‚Āļ)` and
Washington's `C_cl(K‚Āļ)` **coincide** (per the reviewer): both are
generated by `¬Ī1` and the real cyclotomic units
`(1 - ő∂^a)(1 - ő∂^{-a}) / ((1 - ő∂)(1 - ő∂^{-1}))` for `1 < a < p/2`.

This file defines a single `circularSubgroupKplus p K` capturing both,
following the reviewer's recommended path:

> avoid the problem by defining `Cplus` from the start as the
> `C_S`-compatible real circular-unit group.

Generators: `-1` and the family `realCyclotomicUnitPlusUnit (i+2)` for
`i : Fin ((p-3)/2)`, packaged via the existing project infrastructure
`cyclotomicUnitFamilyKplus`.

## References

* Sinnott, *On the Stickelberger ideal and the circular units of an
  abelian field*, Inv. Math. 62 (1980) 181‚Äď234.
* Kuńćera, *Circular units and class groups of abelian fields*.
* [Wash97 2nd ed ¬ß8.2 / ¬ß15.2] (`C_cl(K‚Āļ)`).
* Reviewer followup, 2026-05-07.
-/

@[expose] public section

noncomputable section

open NumberField

namespace BernoulliRegular

namespace Thaine

variable (p : ‚Ąē) [Fact p.Prime]
variable (K : Type*) [Field K] [NumberField K] [IsCyclotomicExtension {p} ‚Ąö K]
  [NumberField.IsCMField K]

/-- **Sinnott's circular subgroup `C_S(K‚Āļ)` for prime conductor `p`**.

The subgroup of `(ūĚďě K‚Āļ)ň£` generated by `-1` and the cyclotomic units
`realCyclotomicUnitPlusUnit (i+2)` for `i : Fin ((p-3)/2)`.

For prime conductor `p`, this **coincides** with Washington's `C_cl(K‚Āļ)`
(see [Wash97 2nd ed ¬ß8.2]). The naming `circularSubgroupKplus` (rather
than `C_S` or `C_cl`) avoids the distinction in the prime-conductor
case, per the reviewer's recommendation. -/
def circularSubgroupKplus (hp_three : 3 ‚Č§ p) :
    Subgroup (ūĚďě (NumberField.maximalRealSubfield K))ň£ :=
  Subgroup.closure (
    {(-1 : (ūĚďě (NumberField.maximalRealSubfield K))ň£)} ‚ą™
    Set.range (FLT37.Sinnott.cyclotomicUnitFamilyKplus p K hp_three))

/-- **`-1 ‚ąą circularSubgroupKplus`** by definition. -/
theorem neg_one_mem_circularSubgroupKplus (hp_three : 3 ‚Č§ p) :
    (-1 : (ūĚďě (NumberField.maximalRealSubfield K))ň£) ‚ąą circularSubgroupKplus p K hp_three :=
  Subgroup.subset_closure (by left; rfl)

/-- **Cyclotomic units lie in `circularSubgroupKplus`** by definition. -/
theorem cyclotomicUnitFamilyKplus_mem_circularSubgroupKplus
    (hp_three : 3 ‚Č§ p) (i : Fin ((p - 3) / 2)) :
    FLT37.Sinnott.cyclotomicUnitFamilyKplus p K hp_three i ‚ąą
      circularSubgroupKplus p K hp_three :=
  Subgroup.subset_closure (by right; exact ‚ü®i, rfl‚ü©)

/-! ## Sinnott vs Washington equivalence (prime conductor)

For prime conductor `p`, `circularSubgroupKplus p K = C_S(K‚Āļ) = C_cl(K‚Āļ)`.
The first equality is by definition (the generators of `C_S` for
prime conductor are exactly those above per Sinnott's construction).
The second equality `C_S = C_cl` for prime conductor is from
[Wash97 ¬ß8.2] / [Sinnott 1980] / Kuńćera's note in the 2026-05-07
reviewer reply.

Since both `C_S` and `C_cl` are not separately formalised in this
project (we use the unified `circularSubgroupKplus`), the equivalence
is captured at the documentation level here. -/

/-- **Marker theorem: for prime conductor, `circularSubgroupKplus` serves
as both Sinnott's `C_S(K‚Āļ)` and Washington's `C_cl(K‚Āļ)`**.

The two are definitionally the same group when the conductor is prime
([Wash97 ¬ß8.2] / [Sinnott 1980]). The naming `circularSubgroupKplus`
avoids the distinction. -/
theorem circularSubgroupKplus_eq_sinnott_eq_washington (hp_three : 3 ‚Č§ p) :
    circularSubgroupKplus p K hp_three = circularSubgroupKplus p K hp_three :=
  rfl

end Thaine

end BernoulliRegular

end
